  <div class="container">
    <h1>Understanding Number Systems</h1>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>What are Number Systems?</h2>
      <p>
        In computer science, number systems are essential for data representation and processing.
        Unlike humans who commonly use the decimal (base-10) system, computers operate using binary (base-2).
        Understanding how to convert between number systems is a fundamental skill in computer science.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Types of Number Systems</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Binary (Base-2)</strong> ‚Äì Uses only 0 and 1. It's the language of computers.</li>
        <li><strong>Decimal (Base-10)</strong> ‚Äì Our everyday number system. Digits from 0 to 9.</li>
        <li><strong>Octal (Base-8)</strong> ‚Äì Uses digits from 0 to 7. Useful in older computing systems.</li>
        <li><strong>Hexadecimal (Base-16)</strong> ‚Äì Uses digits 0-9 and letters A-F. Common in programming and memory addressing.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
